Rioting broke out in Toledo, Ohio after a neo-Nazi march was disrupted by counter-protestors.
The situation escalated with police using tear gas, leading to chaos in the streets.
The leader of the neo-Nazi group claimed they were forced to disband due to violence from protestors.
Mitt Romney expressed disgust at the supremacists' presence.
A man's racist online posts mirrored themes from a notorious novel.
The city faced tensions as Mayor Ford tried to maintain order.
The incident highlighted racial divides and the need for peaceful resolution.
